          "type": "plan",
          "text": "# Test Infrastructure for core-v2, api-v2, cli\n\n## Context\n\ncore-v2, api-v2, and cli have zero tests. Need a standardized, replicable testing approach focused on high-value tests (not 100% coverage). Use vitest + @effect/vitest (both already in root devDeps).\n\n## Scope Decision\n\n| Package | Tests? | Rationale |\n|---------|--------|-----------|\n| **core-v2** | Yes (10 files, ~120 tests) | All business logic lives here |\n| **api-v2** | No | Handlers are 1-liner delegations; typecheck catches wiring bugs |\n| **cli** | No | Thin wrapper — parse args, call service, print JSON. Zero logic. |\n\n## Architecture: What Gets Mocked Where\n\n**Mock the whole repo, not PgDrizzle.** Services depend on repos via `Effect.Service`. Provide `Layer.succeed(DrillRepo, {...})` with mock implementations. This tests: (a) input validation before repo calls, (b) SqlError → parsePostgresError mapping, (c) NoSuchElementException → NotFoundError mapping, (d) success passthrough.\n\n**No repo/integration tests this round.** Repos are straightforward Drizzle CRUD — need real DB to test meaningfully. Defer until Docker/testcontainers setup.\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n### Phase 1: Infrastructure\n\n**1. `packages/core-v2/vitest.config.ts`** (new)\n```ts\nimport { defineConfig } from \"vitest/config\";\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n    coverage: {\n      provider: \"v8\",\n      reporter: [\"text\", \"html\", \"json\"],\n      reportsDirectory: \"./.coverage\",\n      include: [\"src/**/*.ts\"],\n      exclude: [\"src/**/*.test.ts\", \"src/**/*.sql.ts\", \"src/**/index.ts\",\n                \"src/drizzle/**\", \"src/auth/**\", \"src/config.ts\", \"src/kv.ts\",\n                \"src/runtime.server.ts\", \"src/auth.ts\", \"src/type.ts\"],\n    },\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**2. `packages/core-v2/package.json`** — add test scripts:\n```json\n\"test\": \"vitest\",\n\"test:run\": \"vitest run\",\n\"test:coverage\": \"vitest run --coverage\"\n```\n\n**3. `packages/core-v2/src/test-helpers.ts`** (new) — shared fixtures + mock factories:\n- Fixture factories: `makeDrill()`, `makePlayer()`, `makePractice()`, `makePracticeItem()`, `makePracticeReview()` with sensible defaults + overrides\n- Constants: `VALID_NANOID` (12-char), `VALID_BASE64_ID` (32-char)\n- Mock repo layers: `mockDrillRepo(overrides?)`, `mockPlayerRepo(overrides?)`, `mockPracticeRepo(overrides?)`, `mockUserRepo(overrides?)` — each returns a `Layer.succeed(Repo, {...})` defaulting to `Effect.succeed([])` for lists, `Effect.fail(NoSuchElementException)` for single-entity ops\n- Error helpers: `makeSqlError(pgCode, constraint?)`, `makeNoSuchElement()`\n\n### Phase 2: Pure Function Tests (no mocking, highest value/effort)\n\n**4. `src/util.test.ts`** (~15 tests) — `parsePostgresError` + `decodeArguments`\n- Tests every PG error code branch: 23505, 23503 (ConstraintViolation), 23502, 23514, 42501, 08000/08003/08006/53300, 40001/40P01, unknown, undefined\n- Constraint name propagation + defaults\n- `decodeArguments`: valid → decoded, invalid → ValidationError\n\n**5. `src/schema.test.ts`** (~12 tests) — shared schemas\n- NanoidSchema: valid 12-char, wrong length, invalid chars\n- EmailSchema: valid, malformed\n- PlayerNameSchema: valid, empty, too long\n- JerseyNumberSchema: 0, 999, negative, >1000, float\n- SerialSchema, Base64IdSchema edge cases\n\n### Phase 3: Domain Schema Tests (fast, mechanical)\n\n**6. `src/drill/drill.schema.test.ts`** (~10 tests)\n- CreateDrillInput: name minLength, enum acceptance/rejection\n- GetDrillInput/DeleteDrillInput: nanoid validation\n- UpdateDrillInput: publicId required, others optional\n- Enum schemas: Difficulty, Category, PositionGroup, Intensity, FieldSpace\n\n**7. `src/player/player.schema.test.ts`** (~8 tests)\n- CreatePlayerInput: name constraints, email\n- PlayerByIdInput: nanoid\n- UpdatePlayerInput: publicId required, others optional\n\n**8. `src/practice/practice.schema.test.ts`** (~12 tests)\n- CreatePracticeInput: nullable fields, status enum\n- AddItemInput: type enum required\n- ReorderItemsInput: array of nanoids\n- PracticeStatus, PracticeItemType, PracticeItemPriority enums\n\n**9. `src/user/user.schema.test.ts`** (~4 tests)\n- GetUserFromEmailInput: email validation\n\n### Phase 4: Service Tests (require mock infrastructure)\n\nEach service test follows identical pattern using `@effect/vitest` `layer()`:\n- Build test layer: `DrillService.Default.pipe(Layer.provide(mockDrillRepo(overrides)))`\n- Test happy path, NotFoundError path, SqlError→mapped error path, ValidationError path\n\n**10. `src/drill/drill.service.test.ts`** (~15 tests) — template for all services\n- list: returns array, SqlError→DatabaseError\n- get: success, NotFoundError, SqlError, ValidationError (bad publicId)\n- create: success, NotFoundError, SqlError (23505 unique), ValidationError (empty name)\n- update: success, NotFoundError, SqlError\n- delete: success, NotFoundError, SqlError\n\n**11. `src/player/player.service.test.ts`** (~15 tests) — same pattern\n\n**12. `src/practice/practice.service.test.ts`** (~25 tests) — same pattern + extra methods:\n- items: addItem, updateItem, removeItem, listItems, reorderItems\n- review: getReview, createReview, updateReview\n\n**13. `src/user/user.service.test.ts`** (~5 tests) — simplest (1 method: fromEmail)\n\n## File Layout (colocated, matching pipeline pattern)\n\n```\npackages/core-v2/\n  vitest.config.ts              NEW\n  src/\n    test-helpers.ts             NEW - fixtures + mock layers\n    schema.test.ts              NEW - shared schema validation\n    util.test.ts                NEW - parsePostgresError + decodeArguments\n    drill/\n      drill.schema.test.ts     NEW\n      drill.service.test.ts    NEW\n    player/\n      player.schema.test.ts    NEW\n      player.service.test.ts   NEW\n    practice/\n      practice.schema.test.ts  NEW\n      practice.service.test.ts NEW\n    user/\n      user.schema.test.ts      NEW\n      user.service.test.ts     NEW\n```\n\n## Key Source Files\n\n| File | Role in Testing |\n|------|----------------|\n| `packages/core-v2/src/util.ts` | Primary target: `parsePostgresError` is highest-value test |\n| `packages/core-v2/src/error.ts` | 6 TaggedError types used in assertions |\n| `packages/core-v2/src/schema.ts` | Shared schemas (NanoidSchema, EmailSchema, etc.) |\n| `packages/core-v2/src/drill/drill.service.ts` | Template service — all 4 domains share this pattern |\n| `packages/core-v2/src/drill/drill.repo.ts` | Repo interface to mock |\n| `packages/pipeline/src/validate/validate.service.test.ts` | Reference: `@effect/vitest` `layer()` + `it.scoped()` pattern |\n| `packages/pipeline/vitest.config.ts` | Reference vitest config |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\ncd packages/core-v2\nbun run test           # all tests pass\nbun run test:coverage  # see coverage report\n\n# from root\nbun run test           # turbo picks up core-v2 tests\nbun run typecheck      # no type errors in test files\n```\n\n## Unresolved Questions\n\nNone — the plan is self-contained. The `@effect/vitest` `layer()` API for building test layers from mocked repos is the one area where we'll need to verify the exact syntax against the installed version (0.27.0), but the pattern is well-established from the pipeline tests.\n",
