mpose -f ../../docker-compose.test.yml up -d\",\n\"test:db:down\": \"docker compose -f ../../docker-compose.test.yml down\"\n```\n\n## File Layout\n\n```\ndocker-compose.test.yml              NEW (root)\npackages/core-v2/\n  vitest.config.ts                   NEW\n  src/\n    test/\n      db.ts                          NEW - TestDatabaseLive layer (PG, no SSL)\n      setup.ts                       NEW - globalSetup: migrations + truncation helper\n      fixtures.ts                    NEW - factory functions for valid domain inputs\n    schema.test.ts                   NEW - shared schema unit tests\n    util.test.ts                     NEW - parsePostgresError + decodeArguments unit tests\n    drill/\n      drill.integration.test.ts     NEW - Service → Repo → DB\n    player/\n      player.integration.test.ts    NEW - Service → Repo → DB\n    practice/\n      practice.integration.test.ts  NEW - Service → Repo → DB\n    user/\n      user.integration.test.ts      NEW - Service → Repo → DB (skip if no user table seed data available)\n```\n\n**Total: ~12 new files** (3 infra, 2 unit test, 3-4 integration test, 1 fixtures, 1 vitest config, 1 docker-compose)\n\n## Unit Tests (pure functions, no DB)\n\n### `src/util.test.ts` (~15 tests)\n\n`parsePostgresError` — every PG code branch:\n- `23505`/`23503` → ConstraintViolationError\n- `23502` → ConstraintViolationError w/ \"Not null\" detail\n- `23514` → ConstraintViolationError w/ \"Check constraint\" detail\n- `42501` → DatabaseError \"Insufficient privileges\"\n- `08000`/`08003`/`08006`/`53300` → DatabaseError \"Connection error\"\n- `40001`/`40P01` → DatabaseError \"Transaction conflict\"\n- Unknown code → DatabaseError w/ pg message\n- No code → DatabaseError \"Unknown database error\"\n- Constraint name propagation + \"unknown\" default\n\n`decodeArguments` — valid→decoded, invalid→ValidationError\n\n### `src/schema.test.ts` (~12 tests)\n\n- NanoidSchema: valid, wrong length, invalid chars\n- EmailSchema: valid, malformed\n- PlayerNameSchema: valid, empty, >100 chars\n- JerseyNumberSchema: 0, 999, negative, >1000, float\n- SerialSchema, Base64IdSchema basics\n\n## Integration Tests (Service → Repo → DB)\n\nEach integration test file uses `@effect/vitest` `layer()` with the `TestDatabaseLive` + `ServiceClass.Default` layer. Tables truncated between tests.\n\n### `src/player/player.integration.test.ts` (~15 tests)\n\nCRUD lifecycle:\n- `create` → returns player with publicId, name, email, timestamps\n- `list` → returns all created players\n- `getByPublicId` → returns specific player\n- `getByPublicId` nonexistent → `NotFoundError`\n- `update` → returns updated fields, untouched fields preserved\n- `update` nonexistent → `NotFoundError`\n- `delete` → returns deleted player, no longer in list\n- `delete` nonexistent → `NotFoundError`\n\nValidation at service boundary:\n- `create` w/ invalid input → `ValidationError` (never hits DB)\n- `getByPublicId` w/ bad nanoid → `ValidationError`\n\nConstraint behavior:\n- `create` duplicate publicId → `ConstraintViolationError` (unique constraint on public_id)\n\n### `src/drill/drill.integration.test.ts` (~18 tests)\n\nSame CRUD lifecycle as player, plus:\n- Enum fields: create with valid difficulty/category/positionGroup → persisted correctly\n- Array fields: tags, category, positionGroup stored and retrieved as arrays\n- Nullable fields: create with nulls, update to set/clear values\n- `update` partial: only provided fields change\n\n### `src/practice/practice.integration.test.ts` (~25 tests)\n\nPractice CRUD (same lifecycle pattern), plus:\n\nItem management:\n- `addItem` → creates item linked to practice\n- `listItems` → returns items ordered by orderIndex\n- `updateItem` → partial update preserves other fields\n- `removeItem` → deletes item\n- `reorderItems` → updates orderIndex for all items, returns reordered list\n\nReview:\n- `createReview` → linked to practice\n- `getReview` → returns review\n- `updateReview` → partial update\n- `createReview` duplicate for same practice → `ConstraintViolationError` (unique constraint on practice_public_id)\n\n### `src/user/user.integration.test.ts` (~5 tests)\n\nUser has a different table structure (better-auth, text PK not serial). Only 1 service method (`fromEmail`).\n- Insert test user directly via SQL, then `fromEmail` finds it\n- `fromEmail` nonexistent → `NotFoundError`\n- `fromEmail` invalid email → `ValidationError` (actually uses `Schema.decode` not `decodeArguments` — still validates)\n\n## Test Layer Pattern\n\n```ts\n// Each integration test file:\nimport { describe, it, layer } from \"@effect/vitest\";\nimport { Effect, Layer } from \"effect\";\nimport { PlayerService } from \"./player.service\";\nimport { TestDatabaseLive, truncateAll } from \"../test/db\";\n\n// Service with real repo + real DB\nconst TestLayer = PlayerService.Default.pipe(Layer.provide(TestDatabaseLive));\n\nlayer(TestLayer)(\"PlayerService integration\", (it) => {\n  it.effect(\"creates a player\", () =>\n    Effect.gen(function* () {\n      yield* truncateAll;\n      const svc = yield* PlayerService;\n      const player = yield* svc.create({ name: \"Test\", email: \"t@t.com\" });\n      expect(player.name).toBe(\"Test\");\n      expect(player.publicId).toHaveLength(12);\n    })\n  );\n});\n```\n\n## Fixtures — `src/test/fixtures.ts`\n\nFactory functions returning valid domain inputs:\n\n- `validCreatePlayer(overrides?)` → `{ name: \"Test Player\", email: \"test@example.com\", ...overrides }`\n- `validCreateDrill(overrides?)` → `{ name: \"Test Drill\", subtitle: null, description: null, difficulty: \"beginner\", ... }`\n- `validCreatePractice(overrides?)` → `{ name: \"Test Practice\", date: null, ... }`\n- `validAddItem(practicePublicId, overrides?)` → `{ practicePublicId, type: \"drill\", ... }`\n- `validCreateReview(practicePublicId, overrides?)` → `{ practicePublicId, wentWell: null, ... }`\n\nThese avoid repeating boilerplate in every test while keeping inputs explicit.\n\n## 